  "name": "exploration",
  "extends": "../soundtrack.json",
  "_comment": "\"The Long Watch\" — the keep at rest between assaults, the ambient/exploration cue. Patient and sparse: this is the ONE track that never states the hook in full. `watch` is space (a slow string pad and lone bell glints); `vigil` lets the secondary `vanguard` march sound once, distant and low, over a rolling harp; `ember` teases only the HEAD of ember_theme high on the bell (the sacred flame flickering, never the whole hope) before the loop folds back to the vigil. Drive is deliberately absent — the calm that the siege and boss break.",
  "bpm": 80,
  "meaning": "hope",
  "entity": "the-keep",

